it("rejects second cancel attempt", () => {
  _reset();
  const b = createBooking({ petName: "Rex", nights: 1, pricePerNight: 10 });
  cancelBooking(b.id);
  assert.throws(() => cancelBooking(b.id), /already cancelled/); // fails now
});
```

7) **Revenue includes cancelled bookings** (`src/services/bookings.js:55`)  
Cancelled bookings should not contribute to realized revenue.

```js
import { getStats } from "../src/services/bookings.js";

it("excludes cancelled bookings from revenue", () => {
  _reset();
  const kept = createBooking({ petName: "Rex", nights: 2, pricePerNight: 50 });
  const removed = createBooking({ petName: "Luna", nights: 1, pricePerNight: 100 });
  cancelBooking(removed.id);
  assert.equal(getStats().revenue, kept.totalPrice); // fails now
});
```

8) **Mass-assignment / ID overwrite vulnerability** (`src/services/bookings.js:9-10`)  
Because `...data` comes after `id`, caller can set `id` and overwrite identity.

```js
it("does not allow client to overwrite id", () => {
  _reset();
  const b = createBooking({ id: 9999, petName: "Hacker", nights: 1, pricePerNight: 10 });
  assert.notEqual(b.id, 9999); // fails now
});
```

9) **Missing health endpoint** (`src/routes/bookings.js`, comment at line 34-35)  
Operational health checks are absent.

